node.text:
A festive wine-spiked cranberry syrup spooned over goat cheese!!🤩🍷ohhhhh yaaa!🤤Quick, easy and delicious.

Exploring the wines of Paso Robles over here! @roberthallwinery Paso Red Blend composition ... Awesome quality for the price! (around ~$20)
39% Zinfandel
33% Petite Sirah
12% Petit Verdot
9% Tempranillo 
7% Syrah
They’re offering free shipping on 3 or more bottles if you buy from their site with code FREES 🤗 RobertHallWinery.com 
Also, they’re doing the WORLD’S FIRST regenerative case study with leading biodynamics consultant Philippe Armenier! Basically, they are initiating a comparative trial between conventionally farmed vineyards and organic/biodynamic farmed vineyards! Pretty cool!

The 🧀 goods:
•8oz (or more) goat cheese 
•crackers
•5oz. cranberries 
•1/3 cup sugar 
•1 stick of cinnamon of 1 tsp.
•1/2 cup @roberthallwinery Paso red blend
•2 sage leaves 
•1/8 tsp. salt
Combine and sauce pan on low for 10 minutes! 💯Enjoy!🍷🧀🤗

node.title: Holiday Cheese & Wine Pairing for 2 with @roberthallwinery 🍷🧀

node.text:
WINE EXPERIMENT! aka a horizontal tasting with @galeriewines !! We've got the same grape here (100% Cabernet Sauvignon), same vintage (2016), same winemaking style - but the grapes are grown in different locations!! Tasting the differences between Knights Valley, Sonoma County and Napa Valley! 

Recap:
🍷Knights Valley had more powerful tannins, darker fruit smells/flavors and was more earthy. Grapes are grown at the base of Mt. St. Helena which has cooler temps & volcanic soils that produce slower-ripening fruit with distinctive minerality!
🍷Napa Valley had more red fruits, smooth tannins and a fresh acidity that brought that fruit to life! Known for its crazy amazing sunshine hours and rich, fruit-forward wines!

If you’re a front-line worker in Metro-Detroit, these were the wines we gave away as “wine fairies”🧚🏼a few months ago!🤗Jon and I both love them AND the price for a really solid bottle isn't bad either! (~$65). Plus they've got a pretty awesome female winemaker, @femmefermentation 🤩

If anyone wants to try this sort of tasting with me on Zoom - send me a DM! or check out their website, GalerieWines.com - they also do a horizontal of Sauvignon Blanc! Cheeazz to SATURDAY!🍷😃

If you’re ready for a new white wine to love, look no further!✨Excited to be partnering up with @riasbaixaswines for Albariño month and sharing a bit about this region’s history, sub-regions and different expressions of their wines! @winesfromspain 

Anyone else love this grape?🤗If you’ve never had a wine from Rías Baixas - especially if you’re a white wine lover, you NEED to (Over 99% of all wine produced in Rías Baixas is white). They’re super affordable too - the wines in this video are around $20.🤗
.
.
Wines tasted:
💛 @bodegasantiagoruiz 
💛 @pazosdelusco 
💛 @bodegafefinanes
Can find on wine.com or your local wine store should have wines from @riasbaixaswines 🤗

We don’t get to choose the hand of fertility cards we’re dealt…♠️♥️but at-home kits like @oovalife are giving us the tools to play our smartest hand! 🤪

I mean... technology is literally changing the way women experience their fertility journeys and I will forever support that!💛#ad 

I’m testing out this @oovalife “fertility translator” kit... probably in the most non-traditional way possible… since we all know conceiving naturally is not a thing for women with MRKH.🤷🏼‍♀️ But honestly, the word “normal’ should be erased from the fertility world anyways (am I right?)… And I have ALWAYS been curious to know WHEN my monthly cycles are and if they are regular - if you have MRKH, can you relate?😅

Ok, so Oova is an at-home test that measures two key hormones. Luteinizing hormone (LH), which pinpoints ovulation, and progesterone, which confirms that an egg was actually released. Once you scan your Oova strip, you can see all of your data in the smartphone app and track, predict and confirm ovulation over time!🙌🏼

Whether your cycle is regular, irregular, or you’re like me and literally have no idea🤣 -  Oova can help you play your best hand by providing medically trusted data about your levels and timing. Has anyone used Oova? If you want to give it a try JACLYN10 will give you 10% off!

Mannnn if you woulda told me 1 year ago that today I would be working part-time at Jon’s cousin’s perio & implant office ... I woulda said you’re crazy!🤣🦷BUT... I’ve been loving learning something COMPLETELY different than what I’m used to and being able to talk to Jon about what he’s going to be doing during residency! Learning to be a surgical assistant, taking photos of the surgeries and becoming a part of the team has been exactly what I needed to keep my mind moving after the devastation that December threw at us (biggest thank you ever to Jon’s cousin for bringing me on in January)!💛🙏🏼

Ya never know what life is going to throw at you, that’s for sure! Sometimes our biggest tragedies lead us to unexpected places.💛

And now... we’re officially attached at the hip.😂🍷🦷

It’s here!😀🎬🍷Dropping some bloopers for your Insta viewing pleasure lol... So excited to be hosting the tasting portion of the @napavalleywineacademy’s Wine 101 course! Here’s what ya get... 
🍷A 6 sample wine kit (3 whites/3reds)
🍷Live monthly Zoom webinar tasting with me on the fourth Thursday of every month. Come once, or every month if you want to!😀
🍷8 hours of online training (4 modules).

Link in bio to sign up!✨Let me know if you have any questions!😀

node.text:
Today was my daughter’s due date, May 9th, 2021💕but she came into the world sleeping 20 weeks too soon.

I just want to acknowledge the women who have a really hard time with today, you're not alone. Mother’s Day is not a universally happy day for everyone and I hope you treat yourself kindly and do something that makes you happy.💛

I thought this week, this day… was going to be the happiest and most exciting time in our lives. 

But instead… I’m holding onto the memories of her that I will cherish forever and saying goodbye to the future with her I thought I would have. 

Harper was wrapped perfectly in that pink and blue hospital blanket as I held her in my hands. I sat with her in an old wooden hospital rocking chair and remember looking up at Jon and saying… “I feel like a mom… I’m a mom… this is our daughter.”💔

It was sort-of a surreal epiphany moment filled with confusion, love and devastation. Almost like I was trying to convince myself by saying it out loud. And even though she was gone, she was there.💕

So yes, today almost seems like a cruel reminder of what we lost… but I’m choosing to be grateful that she existed. Grateful that I think of her when I watch the sunrise, or when the wind blows the chimes. Grateful that I am her mother. 

Losing her reminded me that life is never guaranteed. So today, while my heart is still beating, I’m choosing to live - because she didn’t get to.💛🌈
